</comment>
                            <comment id="17894141" author="gerlowskija" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2024 10:30:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I noticed we didn&apos;t have a CHANGES.txt entry for this on branch_9_7 - was that intentional?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17894244" author="JIRAUSER305622" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2024 14:59:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To be honest I paid little to no attention to the changelog file, which is my fault that there is no entry yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For many other CLI &quot;fixes&quot; and deprecations we were planning to create one entry that wraps everything up. I believe we could include this in there as well. However, many changes were backported only to branch_9x. Since this is one of the few fixes we backported to 9.7, this may get its own entry in the 9.7 changelog.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914858" author="richm123" created="Tue, 21 Jan 2025 06:17:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Was this ever backported to &lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.apache.org/docs/9_7_0/changes/Changes.html#v9.7.0.bug_fixes&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;9.7&lt;/a&gt; ? I still see the same issue when starting Solr 9.7 with JDK11.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Failed to parse command-line arguments due to: Unrecognized option: --max-wait-secs&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The changelog also has no reference to this bug - &lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.apache.org/docs/9_7_0/changes/Changes.html#v9.7.0.bug_fixes&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://solr.apache.org/docs/9_7_0/changes/Changes.html#v9.7.0.bug_fixes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914959" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 21 Jan 2025 12:04:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue was tagged with v9.7.1, and v9.8. Neither of these version have been released yet. Version 9.7.1 will never be released, as v9.8.0 is already being voted on as we speak.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17915743" author="richm123" created="Tue, 21 Jan 2025 15:43:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Previous comment from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=malliaridis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;malliaridis&quot;&gt;malliaridis&lt;/a&gt; says this bug was backported to 9.7, hence the question.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When is v9.8.0 expected to be released ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17915843" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 21 Jan 2025 22:00:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=richm123&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;richm123&quot;&gt;richm123&lt;/a&gt; It is indeed backported to the 9.7 release branch, and tagged for 9.7.1, which was scheduled to happen, but then it was decided to focus on 9.8 instead. You can follow the 9.8 release effort on the &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:dev@solr.apache.org&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dev@solr.apache.org&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/mail_small.gif&quot; height=&quot;12&quot; width=&quot;13&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; mailing list. The release vote just succeeded tonight so expect it to be announced any day now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17921932" author="anshumg" created="Tue, 28 Jan 2025 22:17:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing after the 9.8.0 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
